<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST : LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
 DEPENDENCY COURT TO GET NEW SITE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Despite objections from people who live across the Long Beach Freeway from the 
proposed site of a court building for abused and neglected children, the 
Monterey Park City Council has approved selling the land to Los Angeles County 
for $3.5 million. 
</P>
<P>
The hilltop site, next to the Sybil Brand Institute, the county women's jail, 
will house the county Dependency Court. Fire inspectors and a grand jury have 
said the court's current facilities, in downtown Los Angeles, are overcrowded 
to the point of being unsafe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
