</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Heavyweight boxer John Bray of Van Nuys will face Irish national champion Sean 
O'Reagan at Caesars Atlantic City tonight as part of the U.S.-Ireland amateur 
dual meet. 
</P>
<P>
Bray, 18, was selected for the U. S. team as a result of his performance 
earlier this month at a training camp at the Olympic Training Center in 
Colorado Springs, Colo. 
</P>
<P>
This is the second international competition for Bray, a 1988 graduate of Van 
Nuys High. Last year he split two bouts on a Scandinavian tour. 
</P>
<P>
The 10-bout dual meet will be televised by cable station TBS at 3:05 p.m. 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Jamal Swinton of Montclair Prep has signed a letter of intent to play football 
next season at Colgate. 
</P>
<P>
The 5-foot-10, 180-pound defensive back intercepted three passes and gained 348 
yards as a running back last fall. 
