<P>
More on Letterman: His uninvited guest -- a woman charged with breaking into 
his home on several occasions -- has been ordered to undergo further 
psychiatric exams to determine whether she understands the charges against her. 
The attorney for Margaret Ray, 36, requested the additional tests after one 
psychiatrist found her competent to stand trial. Ray faces charges of criminal 
trespassing, burglary, possession of marijuana and larceny. She was arrested 
for breaking into Letterman's home in New Canaan, Conn., on Feb. 28. It was the 
second time in five days that she had been found inside Letterman's unoccupied 
house, and last spring, she also had been arrested twice for breaking into his 
home that's about 40 miles north of New York City. Ray will return to court 
March 28 to learn whether the judge believes she is competent to stand trial. 
Aleene Macminn 
