<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPOTLIGHT: SAN DIEGO ENTERTAINMENT BRIEFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Odissi dance, the obscure classical dance form of Orissa, a state on the East 
Coast of India, is rarely seen on this side of the world. However, at 7 p.m. 
Saturday, the Center for World Music and Related Arts will present a full 
evening of authentic Odissi dance at the Black Mountain Middle School. The 
soloist is Nandita Behera, a veteran of the Khajuraho Festival in India and a 
long-time exponent of this exotic art form. 
</P>
