<TEXT>
<P>
Pop singer Jonathon (Chico) DeBarge has been sentenced to five years and eight 
months in federal prison for conspiring to take 2.2 pounds of cocaine into 
Michigan from California. Hoping to convince U.S. District Judge Richard Enslen 
(in Michigan) of his good character, DeBarge, 22, sent Enslen press clippings, 
including one about his anti-drug campaign at a junior high school less than a 
month before his arrest. But the judge countered, "Who have you harmed by your 
hypocrisy?" ALEENE MacMINN 
