<HEADLINE>
<P>
MEASURE TO PROTECT SEALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BRUSSELS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The European Commission on Thursday proposed to extend for an unlimited period 
its five-year-old ban on imports of seal pup skins. The commission, the 
executive body of the 12-member European Community, said its decision was based 
on the Norwegian government's announced intention to resume seal pup hunting as 
soon as the ban expires. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
