<HEADLINE>
<P>
DOGS SHOT AFTER KILLING 7 ANTELOPE IN ST. LOUIS ZOO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ST. LOUIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Seven antelope were killed Thursday by a pack of dogs that got into their 
compound at the St. Louis Zoo, authorities said. When security guards 
discovered the attack on the herd of eight South African springbok antelope, 
they shot one of the dogs to death in the compound. Three other dogs were 
chased from the area and later killed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
