<P>
PALM SUNDAY MARCH IN JERUSALEM CANCELED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
JERUSALEM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Roman Catholic Church has canceled its traditional Palm Sunday procession 
in Jerusalem for the second straight year due to the Palestinian uprising 
against Israeli occupation, a church official said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
The march, due to be held next Sunday, from the Mount of Olives to the Church 
of the Holy Sepulcher in Jerusalem's walled Old City, was a highlight of the 
Christian calendar in the Holy Land and attracted thousands of tourists. 
</P>
<P>
Father Adib Zoomot, secretary to the Latin patriarch of Jerusalem, Archbishop 
Michel Sabbah, said church leaders decided to call off the parade "out of 
concern for worshipers in these troubled times." 
</P>
