<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE PREPS; 
</P>
<P>
BASEBALL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In Empire League baseball openers: 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 6, Esperanza 6 (8 innings, darkness) -- Visiting Cypress trailed 
Esperanza, 6-1, entering the top of the sixth inning, but rallied to tie. A 
two-run double by Bob Hunt and four walks helped aid the Cypress rally. 
Esperanza is 5-1-2. 
</P>
<P>
Katella 6, Los Alamitos 5 (8 innings) -- Katella scored two runs in the top of 
the eighth to break a 4-4 tie. Billy Fitzgerald had a three-run home run in the 
fifth for Katella (4-4) in the league opener at Los Alamitos. 
