<HEADLINE>
<P>
NO. 1 SADDLEBACK WINS TENNIS SHOWDOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Saddleback College, the top-ranked team in the state, defeated Orange Coast, 
the third-ranked team, 6-3, in an Orange Empire Conference men's tennis match 
Thursday at OCC. 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback (5-0 in conference) won five of six singles matches to clinch the 
victory before doubles play: Carl Hinds won at No. 1 singles, 7-5, 3-6, 6-2. Ed 
Peregrino won at No. 2, 6-3, 7-5, Jamil Atacha won at No. 3, 6-2, 4-6, 6-0, 
Gavin Fenske won at No. 4, 6-2, 6-1, and Stan Sanders won at No. 6, 6-3, 6-2. 
</P>
<P>
Hinds and Saunders won at No. 2 doubles, 4-6, 7-5, 6-3. OCC is 4-1 in 
conference play. 
</P>
</TEXT>
