<P>
Trident Contract Awarded: Lockheed Missiles &amp; Space Co., a division of 
Calabasas-based Lockheed Corp., has received a $921.6-million defense contract 
for submarine missiles, the Navy said. The money is to build new Trident II 
long-range nuclear missiles for America's strategic Trident submarines. The 
missile is also known as the D-5. Work on the contract is expected to be 
completed in September of 1991, the Navy said. Lockheed is one of the nation's 
largest defense contractors. The company last year had $3.53 billion worth of 
business in prime contracts with the Defense Department as its eighth-largest 
contractor. 
