<P>
GUARD SLAIN; GUNMAN KILLS HIMSELF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAKEWOOD 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An armored car guard was slain today in a shoot-out at a supermarket with a 
robber who then killed himself after deputies arrived, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The shooting occurred about 9:45 a.m. inside a glass-enclosed entrance of a 
Von's market at 4001 Hardwick St., Deputy Bill Wehner, a Sheriff's Department 
spokesman, said. Customers and employees were in the store when the shooting 
erupted, but no one was injured. 
</P>
<P>
The name of the guard who worked for Armored Transport of California Inc. was 
not immediately available. When deputies entered the store the gunman was lying 
near the doorway with a self-inflicted wound. He died en route to a hospital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
