<P>
WARY OF SOVIET ECONOMY: KISSINGER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former Secretary of State Henry A. Kissinger warned businessmen today against 
investing in the Soviet Union, saying the country is suffering an economic 
crisis. 
</P>
<P>
Kissinger also told a symposium on the Soviet Union that the West should 
maintain its military guard in case current economic reforms fail and Soviet 
leader Mikhail S. Gorbachev is ousted from office. 
</P>
</TEXT>
