NATION; 
</P>
<P>
SOVIET NUCLEAR TEAMS AT U.S. SITES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 10-member team of Soviet nuclear weapon inspectors today conducted a 
"short-notice inspection" at Ft. Sill, Okla., site of training facilities for 
troops operating the Army's Pershing nuclear missiles, the Pentagon said. 
</P>
<P>
A second Soviet team was inspecting a Martin Marietta Corp. manufacturing plant 
in Middle River, Md. The inspections, authorized by the U.S.-Soviet 
Intermediate-range Nuclear Forces Treaty ratified last year, are the eighth and 
ninth such inspections of the 20 allowed each side this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
