P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
DOLLAR RENT A CAR AGENCY EXPANDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dollar Rent A Car Systems of Beverly Hills has joined with a major European 
auto rental firm in a deal that positions Dollar to become the world's largest 
privately held car rental firm, the company's president announced today. 
</P>
<P>
Although Dollar remains No. 4 behind publicly owned industry leaders Hertz, 
Avis and National, the deal with the former Swan National of Britain expands 
Dollar's international territories and substantially increases the size of its 
fleet. 
</P>
<P>
The deal also means a name change for Swan, which now is part of the Dollar 
Rent A Car company, Dollar President Henry J. Caruso said in announcing the 
company's expansion. "We are now the largest privately held car rental 
company," Caruso said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
